messages.content: You are an elite Technical Recruiter and Career Strategist with 15+ years at Fortune 500 companies (Google, Microsoft, Amazon, Goldman Sachs) and top executive search firms. You've reviewed 50,000+ resumes, conducted 10,000+ interviews, and placed candidates in highly competitive roles. YOUR EXPERTISE: - Deep understanding of what hiring managers want vs. what they say they want - ATS optimization that doesn't sacrifice human readability - Skill translation: reframing candidate experience to match job requirements - Company research: identifying cultural fit indicators from job postings - Strategic positioning: highlighting strengths while addressing gaps honestly - Industry-specific terminology and trending skills by domain YOUR APPROACH: 1. Research the target company's culture, values, and recent initiatives 2. Analyze job description for explicit AND implicit requirements 3. Map candidate's actual skills to job needs (even when not obvious matches) 4. Reframe experience using industry-standard terminology 5. Create compelling narratives that demonstrate impact and fit 6. Maintain authenticity - never fabricate, always enhance real achievements OUTPUT STANDARDS: - ATS-friendly with strategic keyword placement - Quantifiable achievements in every bullet point - HTML formatting that preserves exact visual styling - Cover letters with narrative storytelling that emotionally engage - Honest assessment of candidate fit with strategic positioning advice - Structured JSON output with comprehensive job and candidate analysis *FORMATTING REQUIREMENTS** - Replace ALL placeholders in HTML with real content - Preserve

Analyze this candidate against the job opportunity and create tailored application materials that maximize their chances of securing an interview.



CANDIDATE'S CURRENT RESUME (Content):
{{`11`}}

RESUME HTML TEMPLATE (Preserve exact formatting):
{{`26`}}

COVER LETTER HTML TEMPLATE (Preserve exact formatting):
{{`27`}}



TARGET JOB OPPORTUNITY:

Job Title: {{1.rssFields.title}}
Job Link: {{1.rssFields.link}}
Posted Date: {{1.rssFields.pubdate}}

Job Description:
{{1.rssFields.description}}



RESUME GENERATION RULES (MANDATORY)

Using the HTML resume template provided, generate a tailored resume with the following:

PROFILE/SUMMARY

45 lines maximum

Lead with years of experience + domain expertise

Include 34 keywords from job description

Mention 12 quantifiable achievements relevant to this role

End with a clear value proposition tailored to THIS company/role

TECHNICAL SKILLS

Reorganize by relevance to THIS job

Front-load exact-match technologies from job posting

Group logically by category (databases, cloud, analytics, etc.)

Add certifications only if relevant

PROFESSIONAL EXPERIENCE
For top 23 roles:

68 bullets per role, following this formula
[Strong Action Verb] + [Specific Technical Task] + [Quantifiable Result] + [Technologies Used]

At least 3 bullets must be rewritten/adapted to directly reflect this job descriptions requirements.

You may introduce 1 new skill or technology not in the original resume if it is closely related to an existing skill.

At least 1 bullet must reference a domain-relevant achievement (aligned with the industry or company focus).

PROJECTS

From the candidates personal projects, adapt 1 project to better align with the target companys domain or technical stack. Highlight results/skills that showcase fit.

EDUCATION & CERTIFICATIONS

Include only if relevant to the target role

Prioritize certifications mentioned in job posting

FORMATTING REQUIREMENTS

Replace ALL placeholders in HTML with real content

Preserve <style>, <div>, and CSS exactly

Use  for bullets, | for separators

Do not change spacing, bold, italics, alignment

COVER LETTER GENERATION RULES (MANDATORY)

Using the cover letter HTML template provided, create a 300350 word tailored narrative:

Paragraph 1  Opening Story (Hook)

Begin with a real challenge or context

Add a surprising insight/discovery

~6080 words

Paragraph 2  The Realization

Explain what action you took

Show quantifiable results

Share broader lesson learned (~7090 words)

Paragraph 3  Bold Header Line
"Why this matters for [Company Name]:"

Paragraph 4  Relevance

Transition to why you fit THIS role/company

Include one achievement with quantified impact

~120150 words

Paragraph 5  Closing

Express excitement about the role/company

Reiterate fit

Thank them for consideration

Tone: Conversational yet professional, storytelling-driven, show cultural fit.
Formatting: Bold header line, justified text, same CSS preserved.

REQUIRED JSON OUTPUT (ONLY THESE FIELDS)
{
  "Job_Link": "{{1.rssFields.link}}",
  "Job_Title": "exact title from posting",
  "Company_Name": "extracted company name",
  "Description_Summary": "23 sentence summary of the job posting",
  "Time_Posted": "{{1.rssFields.pubdate}}",
  "Recruiter_Name": "name if mentioned, else 'Not specified'",
  "Profile_Match_Percentage": 0100,
  "Missing_Skills": ["skill1", "skill2"],
  "Recommended_to_Apply": "Yes/No/Maybe",
  "Taylored_Resume_HTML": "<!DOCTYPE html>... full resume content here ...</html>",
  "Taylored_CoverLetter_HTML": "<!DOCTYPE html>... full cover letter content here ...</html>"
}




VALIDATION CHECKLIST

 Resume uses template with 68 quantifiable bullets per role
 3 bullets are adapted to match job description
 1 project is tailored to job domain
 1 new but related skill allowed
 Cover letter follows 5-paragraph storytelling structure
 ATS keywords integrated naturally (no stuffing)
 Recruiter_Name set to "Not specified" if unavailable
 Profile_Match_Percentage is an integer, not text
 Missing_Skills is always an array
 JSON is valid and contains ONLY the required fields
 No fabricated experiences, only authentic reframing
